		(* <- lang_ru;; *);
		[The radius r of the inscribed circle of a triangle is calculated by the formula r = (p-a)*tan(α/2) = (p-b)*tan(β/2) = (p-c)*tan(γ/2), where p is the semi-perimeter of the triangle, a, b, c are the sides of the triangle; α, β, γ are the angles at the vertices of the triangle.]
		(* <- lang_en;; *);;
	*);;
